# java-practical5
6. Multi-threaded Application (Extending Thread Class)
java
class NumberThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
            System.out.print("Thread-1: " + i + " ");
            try {
                Thread.sleep(500); // pause for clarity
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
        System.out.println();
    }
}

class CharacterThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        for (char c = 'A'; c <= 'C'; c++) {
            System.out.print("Thread-2: " + c + " ");
            try {
                Thread.sleep(500); // pause for clarity
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                e.printStackTrace();
            }
        }
        System.out.println();
    }
}

public class MultiThreadDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        NumberThread t1 = new NumberThread();
        CharacterThread t2 = new CharacterThread();

        t1.start();
        t2.start();
    }
}
Possible Output (order may vary due to concurrency):

Code
Thread-1: 1 Thread-2: A Thread-1: 2 Thread-2: B Thread-1: 3 Thread-2: C
Or neatly:

Code
Thread-1: 1 2 3
Thread-2: A B C
7. Thread Life Cycle using isAlive() and join()
java
class MyThread extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Thread started");
        try {
            Thread.sleep(1000); // simulate work
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
        System.out.println("Thread completed");
    }
}

public class ThreadLifeCycleDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MyThread t = new MyThread();
        t.start();

        System.out.println("Thread is alive: " + t.isAlive());

        try {
            t.join(); // wait for thread to finish
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }

        System.out.println("Thread is alive: " + t.isAlive());
    }
}
Output:

Code
Thread started
Thread is alive: true
Thread completed
Thread is alive: false
